[normal]Written evidence submitted by [bold]CARE [bold][OLS0077][bold]&#xa0;[bold]About CARE[bold]Summary[bold]●
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]robust age verification before allowing access to age sensitive content on websites, backed up by financial transaction blocking of such websites that do not comply with the requirement, as introduced by the Gambling Act with respect to online gambling
[normal]●
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]a child friendly internet that would filter at the home network level age inappropriate content from ISPs and Mobile Phone Operators unless and age verified adult “opts-in” to adult content
[normal]●
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]More education for parents coordinated by the secretary of state, conducted by industry
[normal]●
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Strengthen the powers of Ofcom and ATVOD, including requiring Ofcom to come up with a code of practice
[normal]The remit of our response and our response objective[bold]The problem[bold]The solution[bold]Self-regulation seems not to be enough [bold]Amendments[bold]Online Safety Bill[bold]Flawed Arguments [bold]Against[bold] Statutory Opt-in[bold]In conclusion[bold]●
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]robust age verification before allowing access to age sensitive content on websites, backed up by financial transaction blocking of such websites that do not comply with the requirement, as introduced by the Gambling Act with respect to online gambling
[normal]●
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]a child friendly internet that would filter at the home network level age inappropriate content from ISPs and Mobile Phone Operators unless and age verified adult “opts-in” to adult content
[normal]●
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]More education for parents coordinated by the Secretary of State, conducted by industry
[normal]●
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Strengthen the powers of Ofcom and ATVOD, including requiring Ofcom to come up with a code of practice
